      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "rationale": "Mesh convergence study performed on three systematically refined meshes (2.1M, 5.8M, and 14.2M cells) using the Grid Convergence Index (GCI) methodology per Celik et al. 2008. GCI for pressure rise QoI was 1.9% (fine-grid) and for NIH was 2.3% (fine-grid), both below the 5% acceptance threshold. Achieved level 3 reflects the systematic three-level study with formal GCI quantification exceeding MRL 2 requirements.",
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/ac/disc-ac-001",
        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "description": "GCI on the finest mesh must be below 5% for all primary QoIs (pressure rise and NIH). Mesh refinement must be systematic with refinement ratio ≥ 1.3. Asymptotic range must be confirmed (GCI ratio within 5% of 1.0).",
        "threshold": "GCI_fine < 5% for pressure rise and NIH; asymptotic range ratio 0.95–1.05"
      }
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "rationale": "Experimental test conditions for the NIH benchmark study are documented in the published protocol with flow rates measured by Coriolis mass flowmeter (±0.5% accuracy) and rotational speed by optical encoder (±2 RPM). Temperature was controlled at 37°C ± 0.5°C. Boundary conditions in the CFD model were set to match the documented experimental conditions within measurement uncertainty.",
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
